3. `signal-profile-not-null-add-share-summary` — sessionId NOT NULL, shareSummary field

## Migration Workflow (Supabase can't do shadow DB)
```bash
cd packages/db
pnpm db:migrate-new <name>   # generates SQL via prisma migrate diff
pnpm db:migrate-deploy        # applies with prisma migrate deploy
```
Never use `prisma migrate dev` or `prisma migrate reset` — shadow DB fails on Supabase.

## What Was Fixed
### Security
- SSL: rejectUnauthorized=false (Supabase CA not in Node trust store; DB_SSL_CA env var enables full verification)
- Security headers in next.config.mjs
- CORS wildcard → settings.app_url in AI service
- Rate limiting: sessions(10/hr), submit(5/hr), map(20/min), reflections(30/hr), activities(30/hr), counselorMeetingPrep(10/hr)
- Input validation on all routes
- Embedding array validated before raw SQL

### Bugs Fixed
- BUG-1: EMBED_PROFILE QStash job unhandled → now implemented
- BUG-4: completedCount counted started sessions → fixed to count completed
- BUG-5: weekKey used wrong math → getISOWeekKey() with proper ISO 8601
- Synthesis idempotency: signalProfile.create → upsert in both submit route and QStash handler
- Duplicate reflection create race condition
- parsePrompts called 3x per render → once

### API
- All 33 routes use apiError() — returns 401/403/500 correctly
- AuthError class with typed status codes

### Privacy
- shareSignals toggle → fans out to all 4 DB fields (shareInterestClusters/shareBreadthScore/shareTrajectoryShifts/shareCharacterSignals)
- shareSummary → new DB field, persists via PUT /api/privacy
- Counselor summary/meeting-prep routes now respect shareSummary
- Privacy reset also sets shareSummary=false

### Maintainability
- COOLDOWN_DAYS in lib/constants.ts (was in 4 files)
- getISOWeekKey in lib/utils.ts (was inline in qstash route, had timezone bug)

